<h1> Tordate is a NEWS website where Users can write their own articles, vote them, and read other's </h1>
<br>
<h3>You have 3 ways of interacting with the website:</h3>
<br>
<b> As a Writer: </b> You must <a href="/users/sign_up"> Sign Up</a>. Think of a subject , get a good image, and some solid evidence. Afterwards <a href="article/write"> write your article </a>.<i>Don't forget to add your sources!</i><br>
<br>
<b> As a Voter: </B> Voter's are Tordate's editors, they can scroll through the Article and vote at different aspects: They can vote the content up, or down (to do so you must sign up). They can Report the article's lack of evidence; or hateful content. And they can add their own counterevidence to the Article to prove it wrong; counterevidence can be voted up or down as well so readers get to see the strongest counterevidence.<br>
<br>
<b>As a Reader: </b> They can choose between different filters to read about the most diverse and best articles being produced, or the newest and fastest article updates on the Web. Reader's experience it's what Tordate it's all about, granting them the most diverse number of viewpoints for every single topic to help them decide for themselves, the fastest generation of content by the people experiencing it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Thanks for reading!<br>
Still got questions? Ask them at out <a href="http://facebook.com/tordate"> Facebook </a>

